&lt;p&gt;An opportunity has arisen for a senior practitioner to work within the Complex Needs Service. The post holder will be a nurse with experience of working with people with learning disabilities and behaviour that challenges and familiar with Positive Behaviour Support and Applied Behaviour Analysis approaches. The Complex Needs Service is part of the Community Learning Disability Service and works closely with the children’s and adult Community Learning Disability Teams across North Wales. Responsibilities include holding a clinical caseload, acting as link practitioner to one of the CLDTs and the supervision and management of junior staff.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The ability to speak Welsh is desirable for this post: Welsh and/or English speakers are equally welcome to apply.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Closing Date: 18/11/20&lt;/p&gt;
